pt.pa.graph

Interface Edge<E,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - Type of value stored in the edge
    V - Type of value stored in the vertices that this edge connects.

    public interface Edge<E,V>
    An edge connects two Vertex of type V and stores an element of type E. The edge may be used in oriented and non-oriented graphs.
    See Also:
    Graph, Digraph

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      E element()
      Returns the element stored in the edge.
      Vertex<V>[] vertices()
      Returns and array of size 2, with references for both vertices at the ends of an edge.

    • Method Detail

      • element

        E element()
        Returns the element stored in the edge.
        Returns:
        stored element

      • vertices

        Vertex<V>[] vertices()
        Returns and array of size 2, with references for both vertices at the ends of an edge. In a Digraph the reference at vertices()[0] must be that of the outbound vertex and at vertices()[1] that of the inbound vertex.
        Returns:
        an array of length 2, containing the vertices at both ends.
